title: Ramen-Veggie Chicken Salad
summary: Ramen-Veggie Chicken Salad might be just the main course you are searching for. For $2.27 per serving, this recipe covers 37% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One portion of this dish contains about 30g of protein, 57g of fat, and a total of 878 calories. This recipe serves 2. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 40 minutes. If you have green onions, napa cabbage, canolan oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the cider vinegar you could follow this main course with the Vinegar Pie as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 74%. This score is pretty good. Try One Pot Chicken & Veggie Ramen, Chicken Veggie Ramen Bowl, and Shrimp and Veggie Ramen for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. One wine you could try is J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling. It has 4.4 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 22 dollars.

productMatches.title: J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling
productMatches.description:
Despite its still youthful freshness it shows the fine fruity Riesling characteristic and an underlying hint of mineral from the blue/grey Devonian slate soil.

Serve this refreshing wine slightly chilled! As aperitif and, especially when more matured, in combination with seafood or poultry.

instructions: Directions                                                                                In a small saucepan, combine the sugar, oil, vinegar and soy sauce. Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 1 minute or until sugar is dissolved; set aside to cool.                                                                                              Meanwhile, break noodles into small pieces (save seasoning packet for another use). In a small skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add the noodles, almonds and sesame seeds; cook and stir for 1-2 minutes or until lightly toasted.                                                                                            Grill chicken, covered, over medium heat for 4-6 minutes on each side or until a thermometer reads 170°.                                                                                            Meanwhile, arrange the cabbage, red pepper, onions and carrot on two serving plates. Slice chicken; place on salad. Top with noodle mixture; drizzle with dressing.                                        Yield: 2 servings. steps.step: In a small saucepan, combine the sugar, oil, vinegar and soy sauce. Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 1 minute or until sugar is dissolved; set aside to cool.
Meanwhile, break noodles into small pieces (save seasoning packet for another use). In a small skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add the noodles, almonds and sesame seeds; cook and stir for 1-2 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Grill chicken, covered, over medium heat for 4-6 minutes on each side or until a thermometer reads 170°.
Meanwhile, arrange the cabbage, red pepper, onions and carrot on two serving plates. Slice chicken; place on salad. Top with noodle mixture; drizzle with dressing.
